2003-05-31 18:39  dan

	* latex-mk.in: on second thought, don't use ". $POST_BIBTEX_HOOK",
	  but rather just "$POST_BIBTEX_HOOK" to allow for any sort of
	  executible to be used rather than just a bourne shell script.

2003-05-29 05:23  dan

	* latex-mk.in: add the option of running a script after a bibtex
	  run.	If the POST_BIBTEX_HOOK variable is set to an executible
	  script, then it is run immediately after a bibtex run.  The
	  script can set the 'exit_status' variable to something non-zero
	  to cause latex-mk to exit.

	  Suggested by Brook Milligan.

